From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Samaresh Kumar Singh <ssam3003@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 4 Mar 2026 12:51:08 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] ggml-cuda: graceful OOM fallback for event creation

When a model is partially offloaded to GPU, the CUDA_Host (pinned
memory) buffer for CPU<->GPU transfers can exhaust the system's pinned
memory pool. The subsequent call to cudaEventCreateWithFlags() would
then fail but was wrapped in CUDA_CHECK(), a fatal abort macro, causing
the llama runner to crash with "CUDA error: out of memory".

Replace the fatal CUDA_CHECK() with an explicit error check that clears
the CUDA error state, logs a warning, and returns nullptr. This matches
the same fallback pattern already used by ggml_cuda_host_malloc(). The
backend scheduler already null-checks every event before use, so
returning nullptr safely skips cross-device event synchronization
without crashing.
---
 ggml/src/ggml-cuda/ggml-cuda.cu | 9 ++++++++-
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/ggml/src/ggml-cuda/ggml-cuda.cu b/ggml/src/ggml-cuda/ggml-cuda.cu
index 5c9dfd032..f4316ef30 100644
--- a/ggml/src/ggml-cuda/ggml-cuda.cu
+++ b/ggml/src/ggml-cuda/ggml-cuda.cu
@@ -4954,7 +4954,14 @@ static ggml_backend_event_t ggml_backend_cuda_device_event_new(ggml_backend_dev_
     ggml_cuda_set_device(dev_ctx->device);
 
     cudaEvent_t event;
-    CUDA_CHECK(cudaEventCreateWithFlags(&event, cudaEventDisableTiming));
+    cudaError_t err = cudaEventCreateWithFlags(&event, cudaEventDisableTiming);
+    if (err != cudaSuccess) {
+        // Gracefully handle the error (e.g when pinned memory runs out during GPU offload)
+        // Returning nullptr simply skips cross-device sync, which the scheduler already guards with null checks.
+        (void)cudaGetLastError();
+        GGML_LOG_WARN("%s: failed to create CUDA event: %s\n", __func__, cudaGetErrorString(err));
+        return nullptr;
+    }
 
     return new ggml_backend_event {
         /* .device  = */ dev,
